After completing this course, students should be able to:

Expected Knowledge Outcomes

1. Familiarize oneself with particular existential and liturgical contexts;
2. Know how to interpret the Bible contextually;
Expected Attitude Outcome

3. Be a context-sensitive and accountable preacher;
Expected Skills Outcome

4. Accommodate different social, existential and liturgical contexts with relevant biblical messages

courses.course_syllabus:
Week 1) Methodological consideration: Biblical text in contexts;
Week 2) Basic biblical criticism(s);
Week 3) Preaching in the Bible;
Week 4) Preaching in the church history;
Week 5-7) Preaching Bible in social, multifaceted contexts: theory and praxis [I & II & III];
Week 8-10) Preaching Bible in existential contexts: theory and praxis [I & II & III];
Week 11-13) Preaching Bible in liturgical contexts: theory and praxis [I & II & III].

